            . I am in the employ of Thomas Slater, a <rs id="t18271206-240-viclabel1273" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-240-victim1289 t18271206-240-viclabel1273"></join>, of <placeName id="t18271206-240-crimeloc1274">Pitfield-street, Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-240-crimeloc1274" type="placeName" value="Pitfield-street, Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-240-crimeloc1274" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-240-off1271 t18271206-240-crimeloc1274"></join>: the prisoner came there on the 30th of November - he asked for some cotton - I served him - he said it was too coarse - I then showed him another ball, which he said would do; he paid me, and went to the shop door - he turned and snatched a parcel of stockings out of the window; he ran away - I called out, but he made his escape then, and was taken the following evening; I am quite sure he is the same boy - he dropped the stockings in the street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271206-240-person1291">
                  MARY 
                  ARNOLD
               <interp inst="t18271206-240-person1291" type="surname" value="ARNOLD"></interp>
